.TH "batadv_send_broadcast_skb" 9 "batadv_send_broadcast_skb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_send_broadcast_skb \- Send broadcast packet via hard interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" batadv_send_broadcast_skb
.BI "(struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_hard_iface *hard_iface "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
packet to be transmitted (with batadv header and no outer eth header)
.IP "hard_iface" 12
outgoing interface
.SH "RETURN"
A negative errno code is returned on a failure. A success does not
guarantee the frame will be transmitted as it may be dropped due
to congestion or traffic shaping.
